&lt;p&gt;Per your debugging message, &lt;code&gt;string(28) "APPROVAL"&lt;/code&gt; your string is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;ssl_result_message&amp;gt;APPROVAL
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;not &lt;code&gt;APPROVAL&lt;/code&gt;, your browser probably is hiding the element. You could either strip the elements if that is really what your complete string is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$value = strip_tags($test123);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or you could use a parser:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$dom = new DOMDocument;
libxml_use_internal_errors(true);
$dom-&amp;gt;loadHTML($test123);
libxml_clear_errors();
$ssl = $dom-&amp;gt;getElementsByTagName('ssl_result_message');
$value = $ssl-&amp;gt;item(0)-&amp;gt;nodeValue;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for an explanation for what your current code did...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The function is defined to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
