&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So your searched for &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;ssl_result_message&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, found it and returned that and the remaining string:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;ssl_result_message&amp;gt;APPROVAL&amp;lt;/ssl_result_message&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;you then took off the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;/ssl_result_message&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; which left you with the 28 character string. A parser is really the best way to handle these type of processes going forward.&lt;/p&gt;
