Answer:
&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You could make an array with your three variables and then validate them with a &lt;code&gt;foreach&lt;/code&gt; loop. Even in the same &lt;code&gt;foreach&lt;/code&gt; loop you could make the first validation you have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;foreach(array($x, $y, $z) as $values) {//---&amp;gt; the $values variable represents each of your '$x, $y, $z' variables in the loop.
    if (empty($values)) {
        $_SESSION["ErrorMessage"]="You have to fill all the blanks.";
        redirect_to("addxyz.php");

    } else if (strlen($values) &amp;gt; 99) {
        $_SESSION["ErrorMessage"]="Very Long  Name for $values";//---&amp;gt; This will notify the first value that fails the validation.
